                                                                                                               Statue protest
                            
	Bangalore, Aug. 8 (PTI): Over 1,000 pro-Kannada activists, protesting the unveiling of the statue of Tamil savant Thiruvalluvar, were arrested across Karnataka today, a day before the inauguration. One protester also ate pesticide.                                                                                                                                                                           
